      "stimulus_html": "",
      "stem_html": "<p>Reaction of (<i>S</i>)-3-methyl-2-pentanone with methylmagnesium bromide followed by acidification yields 2,3-dimethyl-2-pentanol. What is the stereochemistry of the product? Is the product optically active?</p>\n<img class=\"scaled-down\" src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBdmtWIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--83952df611c1aac2d2c833c1953f34dae5752064/OChem_17_EC_044.jpg\" alt=\"The structure of 3-methyl-2-pentanone. It is a five-carbon chain with keto group on C 2 and methyl group on C 3.\">",
